\par \fs26 Kills me not To kill rhem. I mean, I know the whole point is to study their movements, set up an early warning network. I know that if we had the resources to clear them all we would. Still. . .\fs24 
\par \f2\fs22 [He darts a sixth target. Like all the others, this one is oblivious to the small hole in its sternum.]\fs24 
\par \f0\fs26 How do they do it? How are they still around ? Nothing in the world cor\-rodes like saltwater. These Gs should have gone way before the ones on land. Their clothes sure did, anything organic like cloth or leather.\f2\fs24 
\par \fs22 [The figures below us are practically naked.]\fs24 
\par \f0\fs26 So why not the rest of them.' Is it the temperature at these depths, is it the pressure? And why do they have such a resistance to pressure anyway? At this depth the human nervous system should be completely Jell-O-ized. They shouldn't even be able to stand, let alone walk and "think" or what\-ever their version of thinking is. How do they do it? I'm sure someone real high up has all the answers and I'm sure die only reason they don't tell me is ...\f2\fs24 
\par \fs22 [He is suddenly distracted by a flashing light on his instrument\fs24 
\par \fs22 panel.]\fs24 
\par \f0\fs26 Hey, hey, hey. Check this out.\f2\fs24 
\par \fs22 [I look down at my own panel. The readouts are incomprehensible.]\fs24 
\par \f0\fs26 We got a hot one, pretty healthy rad count. Must be from the Indian Ocean, Iranian or Paid, or maybe that ChiCom attack boat that went down oft Manihi. How about that'\fs24 
\par \f2\fs22 [He fires another dart.I\f0\fs24 
\par \fs26 You're lucky. This is one of the last manned recon dives. Next month it's all ROV, 100 percent Remotely Operated Vehicles.\fs24 
\par \i\fs26 There's been a lot of controversy over the use of ROVs for combat.\i0\fs24 
\par \fs26 Never happen. The Sturge's got way too much star power. She'd never let Congress go 'droid on us.\fs24 
\par \i\fs26 Is there any validity to their argument?\i0\fs24 
\par \fs26 What, you mean if robots are more efficient fighters than ADS divers? Hell no. All that talk about "limiting human casualties" is bullshit. We never lost a man in combat, not one! That guy they keep talking about, Chernov, he was killed after the war, on land, when he got wasted and passed out on a tram line. Fuckin' politicians.\fs24 
\par \fs26 Maybe ROVs are more cost-effective, but one thing they're not is \i better. \i0 I'm not just talking about artificial intelligence; I'm talking heart, instinct, initiative, everything that makes us us. That's why I'm still here, same with the Sturge, and almost all the other vets who took the plunge during the war. Most of us are still involved because we have to be, because they still\fs24 
\par \fs26 haven't yet come up with a collection of chips and bits to replace us. Be\-lieve me, once they do, I'll not only never look at an exosuit again, I'll quit the navy and pull a full-on Alpha November Alpha.\fs24 
\par \fs26 2. "The Sturgeon General": The old civilian nickname tor the present commander of the DSCC.\fs24 
