\par \fs26 Action \i in the \i0 North Atlantic, this old, black-and-white war flick. There's a guy in it, you know the "Skipper" from \i Gilligan's Island, \i0 his old man. He had a line . . . "I'm putting an oar on my shoulder and I'm starting inland. And the first time a guy says to me 'What's that on your shoulder?' diat's where I'm settling for the rest of my life."\fs24 
